reviews.title: Not good service
reviews.text:
Ordered 2 Americanos and a cake for my wife, which was okay but the service was terrible. I ordered in french, but the lady who took my order was ignorant. Cake arrived with no plate or fork and no milk. She then disappeared so I had to complain to another member of staff who gave us some milk. 
We quickly finished our drinks and cake and left.
Will not be returning.

reviews.title: Convenient location
reviews.text:
Busy venue not far form the station and Ave De Champagne. We enjoyed an Americano and chocolate muffin. Excellent coffee
Lots of outdoor seating.

reviews.title: Unfriendly coffee
reviews.text: We went there to eat a class and drink a refreshing drink, the waitress was not very nice, fortunately the ice cream was good. But I'm not going back. If I decide to go eat at an establishment and spend my money there, it is not to hear the waitress who works there blow.

reviews.title: Afternoon drinks
reviews.text: Stopped for a drink. Sat on the pavement in the sun and watched the people go by. Lovely cakes etc. Good coffee and fsb icecream. Staff were friendly.

reviews.title: Disappointment
reviews.text: Not kind does not answer hello, pastries too much super sticky topping, no taste.  Run on the cup. The service and quality are not at high reputation. Very disappointed. We're not coming back.

reviews.title: Average Award quality ratio
reviews.text:
The living room is clean and the products are well presented. 
The staff is friendly.
I was disappointed by the Wraps who are not well stocked. (Much more cake than content).

reviews.title: Lovely pastry store/bakery/café in the heart of the city

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!
It’s a privilege to visit the world’s most beautiful oceans. Celebrate World Oceans Day by learning how to protect them.

randomContentList.sponsorDisplayName: the More to Jamaica Community-Based Tourism Project

seoInfo.metaDescription: Experience Jamaica through local eyes. From Maroon traditions and family-run farms to artisan workshops and river tubing adventures, these are the moments that bring the island’s soul to life. Across the island, communities are opening their doors and inviting you in. Travel deeper with locally-led experiences and see a side of Jamaica some visitors miss: authentic, unforgettable, and full of heart.

articleContent.title: The best time to visit Iceland: few crowds, great deals, and blissed-out weather

seoInfo.metaDescription: Not sure which month to visit Iceland? Here's your guide to the best time of year to go to Iceland for Northern Lights, the midnight sun, whale-watching, great weather and more.

Berlin is nothing if not resilient, having outlasted many turbulent periods in its history. Those scars still show today in the stark distinction felt between the east and west sides of the city even though it’s been decades since the Berlin Wall came down. And for a European capital city, it’s not conventionally beautiful like Paris or London. Instead, Berlin embraces its eccentric hodgepodge of grit and glamour.

randomContentList.sponsorDisplayName: Fort Myers – Islands, Beaches and Neighborhoods

tripContent.title: Discover a Fort Myers getaway for the whole family
tripContent.description: Planning a vacation the whole family will love can be tricky. Luckily, the islands, beaches and neighborhoods of Fort Myers have so much to offer kids of all ages. From water activities to wildlife interactions to family-friendly dining options, this memory-making itinerary has something for everyone.

seoInfo.metaDescription: Packed with towering skyscrapers, Gilded Age mansions, vibrant public art, and loads of local pride (go Cubs!), Chicago could easily take days to explore. But if you’re short on time, or visiting for a long weekend, you can do most of the must-sees in three days—all you need is this itinerary.

articleContent.title: Macao Peninsula Uncovered: The Heritage Heart of Macao

seoInfo.metaDescription: Step into the heart of Macao, where heritage and modernity converge in a captivating blend of diverse cultures and colours. Macao Peninsula is the oldest district and epicentre of where Macao’s rich history begins. A wander through its lively streets offers a tantalising glimpse into Macao’s fascinating past and its vibrant present.
